/ /  Thankful  Thursday / /  If I asked you what you could be thankful for today, what would it be? This week I am thankful for... 🙌🏼 Healthy routines: There are some habits that I DON'T want to live without, like getting to bed at a decent time, eating healthier dessert options, and avoiding being in a rush (I try!). But it's SO EASY to stop a habit.. and it takes time to re-build it into your life.  I'm thankful to be beginning again on a few of my basic routines that serve me well, physically and emotionally. 🙌🏼 The Invigorated Life re-release: This SATURDAY! Version 2.0: my ebook The Invigorated Life has had a refresh! If you're ready to take some steps towards into a more ENERGISED and NOURISHED lifestyle, maybe this ebook is for you. The Invigorated Life contains 100 simple, effective ideas you can easily implement into your lifestyle. Creating healthy HABITS, healthy SNACKS, boundaries, productivity... these are just a few topics covered.Small changes can make a big difference! ✌️1/4/17 ✌️ What are you thankful for, friend? I hadn't even thought of it before @alkirahandmade's comment about sunflower seeds - they ARE all differently patterned! Like snowflakes of the ground:) I lined them all up today to check out the theory & then got lost in looking & playing around (hence the photo:)) I wonder what it is about establishing order & patterns that is so satisfying? I find that especially when my brain is racing I end up trying to point it in a useful direction like 'the 2nd draw' or some other devil's-nest area (except paper work - I never want to do that). I thought about the ceramicists that Ai WeiWei employed to make the 100 million handcrafted porcelain seeds (really!) that covered the floor of the Tate Modern - when did it cease to be therapeutic? About 1000 in perhaps? - - - - - #itellstories #sunflowerseed #aiweiwei #sunflowers #itellstoriesthroughobjects #garden #melbourne

Not only were the calls not picked up (the manager finally returned my call before COB and I was told to arrive earlier given that it's my first class) but the studio wasn't even opened (mind you, class was only 35 mins away). Waited for a good 15 to 20 mins and nobody seemed to turn up (knocked and no one answered the door). I even sent a text to the number asking if the studio was open and said that I was waiting in front of the entrance but no one replied. Didn't bother waiting any further in the cold. Now I'm not saying don't ever promote your products or services, but you don't need to do it on every post, every day!  Focus on what your audience wants to see, make it more about getting to know you, why you're in business, who you love to work with, and what it would be like to work with you.  I see too many brands shove promotions down the throats of their followers day after day and wonder why they aren't getting anywhere on social media.  An audience gets tired of constant promos and they will tune out.  If you can allow your audience in, and spend time getting to know them then they will be much more receptive when you do post a promo.

Today.  Now I wouldn't consider what I and the band write to be very reminiscent of twenty øne piløts (with the exception being the one where I sing really fast because I think I can rap), but without this band, I can guarantee I wouldn't be making music and singing until my voice gives out. There are a lot of artists I like, there are a lot of artists I love. But I doubt there will ever be one that means as much to me as tøp. Their music isn't for everyone. It's weird and ballsy and in your face. It's also completely honest, often brutally so. I can't even begin to count the times I've nearly been in tears listening to Goner or Addict With A Pen, the former or which I cried my eyes out to just over a year ago when I saw them live for the first time.  Yes, by that point my band existed. But that night signalled a bit of a turning point for me. From then on, I knew I had to put every bit of my heart and soul into every song I wrote and every performance I did. I'm still working on the whole being brutally honest thing lyrically, but I'll get there.  I've been through some not great times, but twenty øne piløts are the kind of band that showed me I can make the bad things into something beautiful. They showed me I can take something used to tear me down and make it build me back up even stronger.  So yes, today I will wake up early, take a train by myself, wait outside for eight hours, scream my lungs out, cry a lot and have one of the best nights of my life. All for a band. Go ahead and think that's stupid, that's fine. You can think post is the cheesiest, craziest thing you've ever read. But just know that this band means everything to me, and I will love them for the rest of my life. "In My Father's House" from the Ko e Hala Hangatonu: The Straight Path series (2013-2016) made with earth pigments, natural dyes, and tuitui (Candlenut soot) on ngatu (barkcloth) --- Elaborate geometry of pattern unfolded on raw barkcloth. Tongan ngatu is a special form of art collaboratively made by women, by beating the softened inner bark of a hiapo (paper mulberry tree), rubbing natural dyes, and highlighting the motifs with hand painting. --- I loved this because of how magnificent it was to look at. The intricate, detailed patterns are so authentic, and it's a lot coming from a mashup of tree bark, natural dyes, and many pairs of hands. There are many cultures and tribes in this world that can do a lot more than we realize, with stories we have yet to hear. And when a work of art is bigger than you, it gives way for you to see it as what it is: powerful.

Sake is a gift from the land. In other words, it's a local business. Local rice, local water and even the kobo( yeast) used to be picked up from inside the brewery. When you drink it locally, you would feel the spirit of the land directly. That's why it tastes the best. Tomorrow we will present our sake in Melbourne, far from its origin. The sake can't be the same, but we'll do our best. 日本酒は元々「地酒」がほとんどでした。その土地でとれた米、水、そして蔵の中で採取した酵母の助けを借りて生まれ、交通網が発達する前は、その土地でだけ飲まれるものでした。酒と大地は密接に結びついています。湯沢で湯沢のお酒をいただくと、湯沢の大地から立ち昇る力を感じます。湯沢から遠く離れたメルボルンですが、明日からの爛漫フェアでは、少しでもその力を感じていただけるようにしたいと思っています。 #sake  #akita  #yuzawa #ranman  #melbourne  #日本酒 #美酒爛漫

Today I decided (stupidly) to go by MYSELF to Ikea with two kids.  In my defence there was an item I had wanted for a long time on sale at $200 off and there were only 4 in Stock so I had to work fast.  Everything was going OK. I had Leo in the Ergo and Finn was behaving. People had helped me put the boxes on my trolley and I felt I had that shit under control. I then got my car and started to pack the boxes in when I realised they weren't going to fit. WTF! totally didn't think of that and no amount of pushing and manoeuvring was going to get them in. IKEA do have delivery for something close to $100 and wouldn't hold my items for me to come back and collect the rest so I was in a predicament. The lady beside me then offered to drop them at my house as she lived close by.  I have to say what an f&cking legend. That lady could see I was starting to stress, she had kids so she understood and she was willing to take an extra load in her car and drive slightly out of her way to drop them off. I did not know her from a bar of soap but it's people like her that truly make the world a better place so thank you Alli!! To be honest the worst part of this was Leo screaming half of the way home in the car. I pulled over to feed him but still he screamed and it makes me so anxious listening to it that I start to lose my mind a little. Poor Finn just sat there listening to him cry and then started to cry as well.  So here I was stuck in traffic, car full of boxes, with two screaming kids in the back 😂 I am surprised I didn't start crying too.  Pass me a god damn wine. I'm happy to see the end of today! 🍷🍾 (and thank you to Finn for being a good boy! I don't know what I would have done if he was naughty as well)

Princes Park. What a night for a run and what a way to reward myself than drinking from my favourite water fountain. The water fountain that made me find my love for water fountains. With every step I took I yearned more for her crystal goodness. The desire became unbearable but I pushed on as I knew the longer I waited, the greater the sensation would be. I finished and approached the Goddess. Pressed her button to get my fix. Nothing. I couldn't believe it. My heart sank. How could the plumber have let this happen. I felt disgusted. This just shows that no matter how gifted if not nurtured even the best can end up washed up, just look at Shaun Tait. I hope to one day see her back to her best. As I watched this spider crab perch on an underwater ledge it suddenly jumped, as it did it spread it's legs like a parachute before slowly moving like a skydiver to the ocean floor 10 metres below.  Spider crabs are usually seen during the annual migration in Port Phillip Bay, Victoria, Australia. #tbtatCCP Peter Jeffs 'Time and Distance’ — In 2008, we exhibited self taught photographer Peter Jeffs’ gritty and unconventionally composed ‘Time and Distance’. For the mural-sized black and white prints Jeffs converted a heavy-duty enlarger to project his images onto the gallery wall. The show presented flashes of action occurring on Melbourne streets as seen through a taxi window. The irregular framing and life-sized images invited the viewer to participate in the moment. —  Image: Peter Jeffs, ‘Untitled 2 1995—2000/2007 gelatin silver photograph 115 x 174cm #PeterJeffs #Melbourne #2008 #Photography #tbt #TimeandDistance

It may sound obvious (or even silly) but first impressions really do count - especially in business. --- Like a first date, your first business meeting with a new prospect or potential client should be memorable. --- Pull out all the stops. Freshly cut flowers in your office or meeting space, great coffee or cold glass of water, some yummy treats to nibble on or even your favourite blend in an oil burner could be all it takes to turn a drab meeting into a fun one. Or, if you've opted to meet out, make sure you choose a space that serves great food or coffee, has some intimate or quiet areas where you can talk (and be heard) and is filled with natural or ambient light. It helps if the wait staff are friendly and the service is good too. --- These simple, yet significant touches will instantly set your client at ease and show them that you've been considerate of their needs even before you've done business with them. --- Granted this advice won't help you with your sales pitch - but that's a whole other post 😉 . . . . #meeting #meetings #clients #prospects #firstimpressions #sales #salespitch #businesswoman #business #businessadvice #b2b #b2c #agency #agencylife #strategy #strategygame #imaginecre8tiv #melbourne #marketing #content

Io e il gelato al Mango 💞 Mancano 2 mesi all'inizio dell'estate, e con il primo caldo arriva già la voglia di gelato! Quindi per non farmi mancare questo sfizio, mi concedo di mangiare un gelato alla frutta alla frutta, in modo che lo #sgarro sia contenuto.. Spread over two floors 60th & 61st totaling 6,760 square feet, this sprawling four bedroom, four-and-a-half bathroom residence offers both grand entertaining opportunities and luxurious private quarters. Interiors elegantly conceal service functions, balance soaring views and domestic intimacy, and allocate generous space for art.  A private vestibule gallery sets the stage for this elegantly designed residence with Carlisle 8 oversized wide-plank white oak flooring, floor-to-ceiling Starphire UV-coated windows, custom full-height curtains, and nearly 11-foot ceilings with integrated reveals for custom lighting that draw attention to views and light.  Grand double doors open into the masterfully proportioned Great Room with bar that measures nearly 44 by 25 feet, where northern views of Central Park and east and west views of the city skyline are appreciated through the signature faceted faade of floor-to-ceiling windows. Connecting this impressive space to the equally elegant corner formal dining room with sweeping city and East River views is a double volume gallery with sculptural stair leading to the upper levels living quarters.  The beautifully designed eat-in kitchen by Foster + Partners occupies the south west corner of the tower and features wire-brushed oak cabinetry with integrated pulls and bronze detailing, cabinet-fronted Gaggenau and Sub-Zero stainless steel appliances, double ovens, double dishwashers, wine storage, a 160 X 38 center island, and Italian Carrara marble knife edge counter-tops  #NYC, #LUXURY, #PROPERTY, #RealEstate, #MANHATTAN, #montevideo #PuntadelEste #Toronto #UnitedKingdon #londoncity #Thailand #UAE #Indonesia #AbuDhabi #Tanzania #PalmBeachFl #France #Italy #BERNE #Suisse #Zurich #Brasil #MELBOURNE

Frogmore Stew is considered a classic Low Country South Carolina dish. This dish is also know as Low-Country boil, Tidewater Boil, and Beaufort Boil. Frogmore Stew gets it's name from a place that has only a post office on one side of the road and a two-story white country store on the other. This is the perfect recipe for entertaining, you just throw in the ingredients in different stages, then pour out onto paper. The guests pick at the juicy corn and tasty prawns. This was a mini version for 3, the size is only limited by the volume of your stock pot. 👌🏻🦐🦐🦐🦐

Jabba | Part 4 Q: What are some difficult periods that you’ve been through in your life? And what tools did you use to progress through that? A: “Personally I’ve been pretty lucky, I haven’t really had any hard times. I’ve been really fortunate, I’ve never had any tragedies surrounding me or anything. One thing I did find really hard was when my younger sister developed an eating disorder when she was in her early teens. In those pubescent years where girls are pretty susceptible to that, that was really hard. I didn’t want to get offside and look like I was trying to make her eat because she just would not eat at home, I just wanted to be her friend but then also wanted to help her somehow, that was hard. What was good about is was that I spoke to the rest of my family and we all started to take it seriously. We thought about how we were going to approach the situation and eventually we got her to see a doctor, which sort of scared her a little bit, after being told she was malnourished. That kind of opened her eyes a bit and she bounced back from there and has been fine ever since. I think the most important thing was having the support of the whole family.

For fucks sake..How do you even instagram? Literally forgot I kind of have this thing where I tell you all the useless bits that happen to me these days. So here's this moody pic of one of the vineries at @visityarravalley_official. Do you need a photographer by any chance? Keen like a bean, tbh. // Foo Fighters – These Days🎶 Вспомнила о наличии у себя инстаграма, решила, что неплохо бы отметиться, а то слухи ходят, когда не тыкаешь людям в нос своими картиночками, про тебя забывают, забивают. На фото мрачновато-прекрасный интерьер одной из виноделен, на которые мы с маман ездили. Вот чесс слово, нахожусь в том состоянии, чтоб взять, уехать за холмы топтать виноградик и снимать видосы, ведь алкоголь никогда не перестанет быть популярным 🙃В отличии от инсты, которая у меня в расписании в последние дни была нифига не популярна😁 Почему пропадаю? Как с этим жить? Узнаете в следующей серии! Шутка. Раз чешу языком, дочешу до конца. Мама уехала и как-то тяжело далось вхождение в свой прежний ритм, все-таки чтоб быть взрослым и еще инстаграммером нужен особый скилл. На работе сижу до вечера, разбирая рецепты кофейные и изучая обжарку. Интересно. Надоело, жуть. А вчера ходила на фестиваль камеди, было дико круто! Комедиант еще раз подтвердил, что быть смешным не один раз в неделю, а семь - искусство. Какая-то такая жизнь! Люблю, скучаю, скоро высылать буду вам открытки и кому повезет ченить еще, корочку арбузную например. Ведь главное внимание!👌🏻

14.6k Run For The Kids 👊 Despite the wind and rain I managed to run the entire course 😍 which I am super stoked about as I let my cardio training slip a bit towards the end... and didn't run further than 6k in my training! Although I kept my strength training up and made sure my eating was 90% whole foods and 10% treat myself 🤗 Honestly though if this was me 2 years ago I would of told myself that It was impossible, looked outside at the weather and would of gone back to sleep... never would I of imagined 2 years later I would jump out of bed excited to do a run, it's amazing what a lifestyle change of nutritious whole foods and regular exercise can do to you're mind set ✨

Roti prata and Malaysian food for lunch. Prata was delicious (not too oily and just the right amount of flakiness and bite to it), Mee Goreng was really tasty (though the one at killiney earlier in the week had a better balance of flavours), and the Satay (though humongous) actually smelled authentic and tasted as close to the real thing amongst all the satays i've tried here so far. It's still no where near the taste of the satay that I grew up with, but it'll do. The ayam was fragrant and had a nice char to it, but out of the lot was my least fav.  That said, everything I've had today was nice.  #melbournefoodie #melbourneeats #melbournelife #melbourne #foodstagram #prata #roticanai #eattheworld #instafood #sundaybrunch #rotiroad

One very common reason people have for not travelling is “I don’t have anyone to go with.” That’s not a reason. It doesn’t even make sense.  To me, travel is a personal experience. It’s a chance to learn about yourself; who you are and what you want from life. It allows you to see how different the world is and to put your life in perspective. When you remove yourself from your life back home, you’re able to take that time to reflect and see things in your life a little differently.  And then, when you are alone, there are no limitations. You can go north or south, by boat or by train, you can just sit on the street for the whole day and watch the world go by. There are no rules, no one hour lunch breaks. There’s no one else to worry about and no one checking up on you.  For once, you can finally just ask yourself what you want to do today, and then do it. In the process, you’ll learn things about yourself that will surprise even you. Just like Henry David Thoreau said "The man who goes alone can start today; but he who travels with another must wait until that other is ready.” #VeraFlyto #melbourne #australia . . . . . . . . . . . . . #awesome_earthpix #exklusive_shot #exploretocreate #folkscenery #livefolkindonesia #livefolk #liveauthentic #bevisuallyinspired  #thelensbible #GarudaIndonesia #crew #cabincrew #crewlife #flightattendant #pramugari #airlines #dagelan @dagelan #ivgcomedy #ngakakkocak  @ngakakkocak #feedbacknation #fbn10k #justgoshoot #lf10k #exploremelbourne #modernoutdoorsman #discoverearth #awesome_shots

The best thing about where I live is that at the same time we moved in the developers planted out the park across the road with olive trees! 7years on and I get to enjoy the spoils 😬 I managed to find a gap in today's inclement weather and go for a stroll to pick 5kg of olives in less than half an hour 😁👍I can not wait to trial a few different recipes and methods of curing!

All the hops in our mixed fermentation Saison were added at flame out. A blend of Galaxy and Hallertauer Blanc to hit 25IBU after a 20min whirlpool. Luckily we managed to get the hops in and the lid on the kettle just before the sky's opened up and rained out the brew session.

Today was one of those days that I just couldn't control my thoughts.  I've watched "13 reasons why" and all I can say is that I'm overwhelmed with all kinds of emotions!  I remembered my experiences in high school and in life. And what I can say is, please, be kind to one another, we never know what's going on in someone else's life!  And given to the fact that the conception of right or wrong is different for each one of us, my message is clear... Doesn't matter who you are, just don't do to others what you wouldn't like them to do with you! Wish you all a life full of love!

This might sound crazy, but since I gained full appreciation that all energy in our world is conserved, I have a certain calm around my own fate. . It's calmed my concept of death and loss in general. . Everything, at the core, is energy - scientifically. And energy can not be created nor deleted. It can only change form. . I've worked with clients who have 'lost' loved ones and by the end of the consultation we always find a beautiful love story of exchange - never of loss. It's truly beautiful. ❤️

Saya tidak pernah jemu mengambil gambar graffiti di Hosier Lane, Melbourne kerana hasil seninya akan bertukar hampir setiap minggu. Salah satu gambar graffiti yang menjadi kegemaran saya sehingga ke hari ini ialah wajah pelakon The Dark Knight yang membawa watak The Joker iaitu Heath Ledger yang saya rakamkan pada tahun 2012. Jika beliau masih hidup, usianya menjangkau 38 tahun pada 4 April lalu. Mungkin keistimewaan lain yang menyebabkan saya menyukai graffiti pelakon Hollywood yang juga terkenal dengan lakonannya di dalam filem Brokeback Mountain ini ialah kerana beliau lahir dan dibesarkan di Perth, Australia Barat.  #heathledger #thejoker 📷 2012

Last night we were lucky enough to be taken to a local kushi katsu (deep fried skewers) restaurant by a good friend from my Tokyo Tina days.  This gem of deep fried goodness blew our minds, after talking to the owner we found out the place has been open for 44 years doing the same type of deep fried skewers and only being able to sit a maximum of 8 people at one time.  Watching her cook methodically, clean and entertain us as she was the only one the in the kitchen was simply amazing. She reminded me of Mr Miyagi, friendly and always up for a laugh but a master of her craft 😂

✨💗Mural Artist wanted✨💗 A local (Fitzroy) not for profit organisation is requiring a mural on the inside of a roller door for its Celebrating Abilities organisation, that helps adults and children with disabilities.  The imagery does not need to relate to the organisation but does need to be inspiring and beautiful. The piece will be featured in an upcoming video advertising the organisation on Channel ten, The Project. We will also promote your work and your contribution.  Due to the organisation being a not for profit it is a volunteer job. The artist will get a free one on one training session and paint supplies may be paid for. It's a great opportunity to support an amazing organisation!  We are needing someone asap and available to create a wonderful piece within two weeks.  If yourself or another artist is interested please tag them in this post.  Here is a few links to the organisation.  http://celebratingabilities.org.au  @celebratingabilitiesmelbourne #melbourne #art #artist #mural

Flinders station. The main station building, completed in 1909, is a cultural icon of Melbourne, with its prominent dome, arched entrance, tower and clocks one of the city's most recognisable landmarks. It is listed on the Victorian Heritage Register. The Melburnian saying "I'll meet you under the clocks" refers to the row of clocks above the main entrance, which indicate the time-tabled time of departure for trains on each line; another saying, "I'll meet you on the steps", refers to the wide staircase underneath these clocks. Flinders Street Station is responsible for two of Melbourne's busiest pedestrian crossings, both across Flinders Street, including one of Melbourne's few pedestrian scrambles.  #flinders #flindersstreets #melbourne #heritage #clocks #victorianheritage #visitmelbourne

April is Rosacea Awareness Month☺️ • • Rosacea, or acne rosacea, is a non-contagious skin inflammation that exclusively affects the face.  The small surface blood vessels (capillaries) of the skin enlarge, giving the appearance of a permanent flush. The forehead, cheeks and chin may develop yellow-headed pimples. This is today's made-up bedtime story I told my dog Milli.  What Milli Saw: Milli The Best Dog was troubled. It was wild, windy and wet outside. The tree out the front of the house was dancing like those big guys outside the car selling place with the gangly arms up and funny heads. So much dancing but just wind music. She was troubled because she was warm and cosy. She had a full tummy and a soft fleecy woobie (some people call them a security blanket). But nice, gentle Andrew with the sore eyes who lives outside Coles would be outside in the rain. So would Brendon who says hello to everyone and sleeps in the bookshop doorway. Milli was so sad. The next day she gathered all the hotel owners together and told them they had to give any unoccupied rooms to people and dogs and cats and animals except nasty rats. Everyone deserves a woobie. It was called the Milli Woobie Decree. #melbourne #story #doglover #doglife #dog #winter #homeless #australia

#authenticselfie  This weekend was a time of reflection with some of my closest friends. We drew a picture of ourselves and then passed it round and we all wrote what we love about each other. Then it came time to write about ourselves, and that's when it got hard for some of us. It was so easy to build each other up but society tells us we shouldn't think we are wonderful, we are full of ourselves if we do. I think knowing qualities that make us amazing is so empowering and let's us do good in this world. Only thinking negative thoughts about ourselves only hold us back. I challenge you to tell me what you like about you!

'HWY' is the second album from Melbourne rock band, Dave Wright & the Midnight Electric. After the release of their debut album,'The Lucky Country' in 2014, they entered SAE studios, South Melbourne,between August and October of last year and recorded 'HWY'. #HWY is a bona fide rock album. It's as simple as that. The album contains 8 songs as listed: 'Coming Home' 'Sweet Caroline' 'Where the Needle Hits the Red' 'Avenues of Honour' 'Happiness' 'Bigger than the Two of Us' 'Rain' 'HWY' There are too many highlights to mention here on this album.  However a couple that simply cannot be overlooked  include 'Avenues of Honour'. Written about the returned soldiers and avenues of trees planted in the fallen soldiers honour, this song may just prove to be a defining moment in Wright's career. 'HWY' is another exceptional song from the album. The song peaks with the guitar pairing of Wright and Robert Barber letting lose and cranking things up on their respective Rickenbacker and Fender Telecaster guitars. The album is available now on limited edition yellow/gold vinyl. It'll also be available in limited numbers on Record Store Day, coming up on April 22. The CD is also available now from independent music stores including Readings, Rocksteady Records in Melbourne and from RSD, Paradise Records in Brunswick,  If your forte is listening to albums that are made to be turned up loud and shared with your neighbours, then, 'HWY' is the album for you! @midnight_electric @timcavroxx @rosso_emperor @thatneilsalmon @johnbryant1196  #vinylnerd #vinylporn #vinylgeek #vinylcollection #vinyljunkie #colouredvinyl #indierock #vinylcollection #vinyljunkie #spin #vinycommunity #vinyloftheday #spinningvinyl #spinning #vinyloftheday #vinylgram #vinylrecords #turntables #vinyljunkies #vinylfreak #vinylporn #turntable #record #melbourne #rockmusic #rsd #rsd2017 #dwme #davewrightandthemidnightelectric
